ClickFix:
  Clickfix is a social engineering + script-based attack, in which the attacker tricks the user to run
  Malicious commands in (Run dialog/Powershell/Terminal/cmd).

  Instead of exploiting the softwares, the attacker makes the user to execute commands themselves by 
  luring them into Fixing something like:
    -   "Fix your PC"
    -   "Update browser"
    -   "Install codec"
    -   "Captcha verification"
    -   "Zoom audio fix"

Victim copies command → runs it → malware downloads.

CLICKFIX ATTACK FLOW:

Website / Email lure
        ↓
Fake instruction "Press Win + R"
        ↓
User pastes command
        ↓
PowerShell / CMD executes
        ↓
Payload downloaded
        ↓
Second stage executed
        ↓
Persistence / C2 connection



